answer: It depends: Yes if the northward 100 km leg does not reach or cross the North Pole (i.e., if the start is at least 100 km from the North Pole). If the north leg crosses the North Pole (start is within 100 km of the Pole but not exactly at it) the helicopter will not return to the starting point. If the north leg ends exactly at the Pole the east/west instructions are undefined and the outcome is ambiguous.
